When creating sections in Confluence pages, we have the option to select 'Add section', which allows us to have as many sections in the page as we need.

However, this button always add a section below the current one. This forces the user to first create a section and then to move a section up, in case they want it above the first section.

I suggest adding 2 buttons, 'Add section above' and 'Add section below', so the users can more easily add sections, specially the first one, without needing two clicks.

